1.   Definitions

In this Licence, the following terms have the following meaning:

—   ‘The Licence’: this Licence.

—   ‘The Original Software’: the software distributed or communicated by the Licensor under this Licence, available as Source Code and also as Executable Code as the case may be.

—   ‘Derivative Softwares’: the softwares that could be created by the Licensee, based upon the Original Software or modifications thereof. The extent of modification or dependence on the Original Software required in order to classify a software as a Derivative Software is determined by copyright law applicable in the country mentioned in Article 15.

—   ‘The Software’: the Original Software or its Derivative Softwares.

—   ‘The Source Code’: the plain text version of the Software which is the most convenient for people to study and modify.

—   ‘The Executable Code’: any code which has generally been compiled and which is meant to be interpreted by a computer as a program.

—   ‘The Licensor’: the natural or legal person that distributes or communicates the Software under the Licence.

—   ‘Contributor(s)’: any natural or legal person who modifies the Software under the Licence, or otherwise contributes to the creation of a Derivative Software.

—   ‘The Licensee’ or ‘You’: any natural or legal person who makes any usage of the Software under the terms of the Licence.

—   ‘Distribution’ or ‘Communication’: any act of selling, giving, lending, renting, distributing, communicating, transmitting, or otherwise making available, online or offline, copies of the Software or providing access to its essential functionalities at the disposal of any other natural or legal person.

—   ‘Discriminatory Distribution’ or ‘Discriminatory Communication’: any act of Distribution or Communication as defined above, that restricts, blocks or otherwise limits, or attempts to do so, by any technical or legal mean, the access of any natural or legal person to the Software or copies thereof, on grounds such as sex, age, race, ethnicity, nationality, citizenship, disability, mental illness or ability, sexual orientation, gender, gender identity/expression, religious, creed, or individual political opinions, regardless of weather it is done wilfully or by complying with a local law.

—   ‘Non-Discriminatory Distribution’ or ‘Non-Discriminatory Communication’: any act of Distribution or Communication that is not Discriminatory.

