The grant of the rights mentioned above is subject to some restrictions and obligations imposed on the Licensee. Those obligations are the following:

Attribution right: The Licensee shall keep intact all copyright, patent or trademarks notices and all notices that refer to the Licence and to the disclaimer of warranties. The Licensee must include a copy of such notices and a copy of the Licence with every copy of the Software he/she distributes or communicates. The Licensee must cause any Derivative Software to carry prominent notices stating that the Software has been modified and the date of modification.

Copyleft clause: If the Licensee distributes or communicates copies of the Original Softwares or Derivative Softwares, this Distribution or Communication will be done under the terms of this Licence or of a later version of this Licence unless the Original Software is expressly distributed only under this version of the Licence — for example by communicating ‘NDPL v. 1.2 only’. The Licensee (becoming Licensor) cannot offer or impose any additional terms or conditions on the Software or Derivative Software that alter or restrict the terms of the Licence.

Non-Discriminatory clause: If the Licensee distributes or communicates copies of the Original Softwares or Derivative Softwares, this Distribution or Communication must be done in a Non-Discriminatory manner as defined in Article 1 of this Licence. Should the Licensee's obligations under any local law conflict with his/her obligations under the Non-Discriminatory clause of this Licence, the obligations of this Licence shall prevail. This Non-Discriminatory clause is an essential part of the Licence and a condition for the grant of any communication, distribution, or sublicense rights to the Software.

Provision of Source Code: When distributing or communicating copies of the Software, the Licensee will provide a machine-readable copy of the Source Code or indicate a repository where this Source will be easily and freely available for as long as the Licensee continues to distribute or communicate the Software.

Legal Protection: This Licence does not grant permission to use the trade names, trademarks, service marks, or names of the Licensor, except as required for reasonable and customary use in describing the origin of the Software and reproducing the content of the copyright notice.

